IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: SINCE 1890, WHITWORTH HAS HELD FAST TO ITS FOUNDING MISSION OF PROVIDING "AN EDUCATION OF MIND AND HEART" THROUGH RIGOROUS INTELLECTUAL INQUIRY GUIDED BY DEDICATED CHRISTIAN SCHOLARS. RECOGNIZED AS ONE OF THE TOP REGIONAL COLLEGES AND UNIVERSITIES IN THE WEST, WHITWORTH UNIVERSITY HAS AN ENROLLMENT OF 2,989 STUDENTS AND OFFERS 60 UNDERGRADUATE AND GRADUATE DEGREE PROGRAMS. IN RECENT YEARS, WHITWORTH HAS ENJOYED RECORD LEVELS OF STUDENT ENROLLMENT AND RETENTION, THE STRONGEST FINANCIAL POSITION IN THE UNIVERSITY'S HISTORY, AND INCREASED EXTERNAL VISIBILITY.
IRS990.MissionDescription: Since 1890, Whitworth has held fast to its founding mission of providing "an education of mind and heart" through rigorous intellectual inquiry guided by dedicated Christian scholars.
IRS990.Description: Instruction: Whitworth University's Enrollment (2009-10) Undergraduate: 2,700; Graduate: 289.Under-Represented Ethnic Enrollment Undergraduate: 18.4 percent. Six-Year Graduation Rate (2009-10): 79.3 percent of first-time, full-time students enrolled in fall 2004 graduated within six years. Freshman-to-Sophomore Retention Rate (2009-10): 85.4 percent. The university offers 60 undergraduate and graduate degree programs; the most prominent are Accounting, Education, Art and Music. Whitworth is over 60% done with the new Chemistry and Biology academic building project at a cost of $31.0 Million.

Activity2.Description: Student Services: Whitworth's Residence halls and/or on-campus houses/apartments accommodate over 1,400 students (Fall 2010). Whitworth has a two-year residency requirement. Whitworth's newest residence hall, currently known as East Hall, was dedicated in September 2009. The building is the academic-year home to 170 Whitworth students. Student clubs and organizations: Whitworth has nearly 40 student clubs, ranging from Amnesty International to the Hawaiian Club. Recent Student Highlights: 2010 President's Cup winners (who maintained a 4.0 GPA throughout their college careers) six students. One of those students also received a full-tuition scholarship and a stipend to conduct research in the Lasers and Applied Physics Doctorate Program at Princeton University. The award amounts to $65,000-70,000 per year for up to six years. Three 2010 graduates have been awarded Fulbright assistantship grants to teach English as a foreign language in Argentina and Malaysia, and Belgium. Also In 2010, Whitworth's student-run newspaper, The Whitworthian, won first place in its division at the 2009 National Mark of Excellence Awards, sponsored by the Society of Professional Journalists; for the sixth time in the past 12 years, the Whitworth Jazz Ensemble was named Outstanding College Band at the Lionel Hampton Jazz Festival.

Activity3.Description: Auxiliary Services: Whitworth University provides dining services to over 1,400 students resident students and to the many other students who live off campus, the university also provides access to purchasing books and supplies at its campus bookstore. In fiscal year 2010, the auxiliary services generated gross revenues of over $11.0 Million that supported the academic and students services provided to 2,989 undergraduate and graduate students registered at the university.

Form990ScheduleCPartIV.Explanation: THE UNIVERSITY HIRED A PROFESSIONAL LOBBYING FIRM TO FURTHER A FEDERAL APPROPRIATION INITIATIVE FOR FUNDS FOR A FUTURE WHITWORTH SCIENCE BUILDING PROJECT. THE UNIVERSITY ALSO BELONGS TO THE INDEPENDENT COLLEGES AND UNIVERSITIES OF WASHINGTON STATE AND AS SUCH PARTICIPATES IN THE LOBBYING ACTIVITIES OF SUCH ORGANIZATIONS. Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.ReturnReference: Description of Uncertain Tax Positions Under FIN 48:
Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: In accordance with the accounting standard on Accounting for Uncertainty in Income Taxes, the University addresses the determination of whether tax benefits claimed on a tax return should be recorded in the financial statements. Under this guidance, the University may recognize the tax benefit from an uncertain tax position only if it is more likely than not that the tax position will be sustained on examination by taxing authorities, based on the technical merit of the position. Examples of tax positions include the tax-exempt status of the University and various positions related to the potential sources of unrelated business taxable income. There were no significant unrecognized tax benefits identified or recorded as liabilities during fiscal year 2010. Open tax years subject to examination by the U.S. taxing authorities are for the years 2007 to 2009, which statutes expire in 2010 to 2012, respectively.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 1
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Executive Committee of the Board of Trustees (Board) consists of the President, Chairperson, Vice Chairperson(s), Secretary, Treasurer, the Chairperson and Vice Chairperson of each standing committee and two members at large designated by the Board. The Executive Committee acts during intervals between meetings of the Board and is subject to the control and direction of the Board at all times. During such intervals, and subject to such control and direction, the Executive Committee has and may exercise all of the authority and powers of the Board in the management and affairs of the University, subject to such limitations as the Board may impose. The Executive Committee shall meet when called by the Chairperson. Seven members of the Executive Committee shall constitute a quorum at meetings of the Executive Committee. The Executive Committee keeps regular minutes of its proceedings and reports the same to the Board.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 6
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The members of the corporation shall be the president and those individuals who are members of the board of trustees of the corporation.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Board of Trustees has delegated the review responsibility to its Audit Committee. Once the review is completed the 990 will be set in a secure website for the Board's inspection and review before filing the 990.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Staff and faculty: We tie the completion of the conflict of interest disclosure form to being able to authorize or request any transaction for the university at the beginning of the fiscal year. This is tracked in a database. Trustees: The secretary of the Board, ensures that every trustee completes the disclosure form every fall meeting. If anyone's form is missing, she or her assistant follow up until the form is completed. Then, the Audit Committee reviews those forms with disclosed conflict during the fall meeting for the staff and faculty and during the spring for trustees.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Compensation for key officers reporting to the president was reviewed by the Executive Compensation Committee of the board of trustees in June 2009; this process involved an independent analysis by an outside consultant who compared compensation for these individuals against peer institutions. These key employees include the vice president for academic affairs, the vice president for student life, the vice president for planning, the vice president for admission and financial aid, and the vice president for finance and administration. Compensation for the president was reviewed by the Executive Compensation Committee of the board of trustees in April 2010; this process involved an independent analysis by an outside consultant who compared compensation for these individuals against peer institutions.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Governing documents and conflict of interest statements are available upon request. Fianancial statements are available at the university's website
The oversight and selection process has not changed from prior year.
